## Build & release tooling

- Mobile builds use **EAS Build** (cloud, not local). Invoke with `npx eas-cli ...` (already cached). Production builds: `eas build --profile production --platform android|ios`.
- `WiamAppMobile/app.json` currently has placeholder `extra.eas.projectId: "wiamapp-mobile"` ŌĆö `eas init` rewrites this to a real UUID on first run.
- Mobile Play Store flow is documented in `WiamAppMobile/docs/PLAY_RELEASE_CHECKLIST.md`. Don't duplicate that checklist; track progress against it in `docs/AGENT_MEMORY.md`.
- EAS build commands and local dev setup: `WiamAppMobile/docs/EXPO_BUILD.md`.

## Conventions

- Don't break the QA workflow's free-tier budget (~1640m/month current, ~360m headroom). New scheduled jobs cost ~30 ├Ś runs/day minutes/month.
- Production API base in mobile apps is `https://wiamapp.com/api/v1` (set via `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` in `eas.json` per profile). The `api.wiamapp.com` subdomain is broken (DNSŌåÆ127.0.0.1); do NOT use it.
- The QA workflow's `playstore-readiness` step is the source of truth for "does WiamApp still pass static Play gates" ŌĆö keep `app.json` aligned with it.
- Privacy policy: `https://wiamapp.com/privacy` (must stay 200). Terms: `https://wiamapp.com/terms`.
- **Email roles:** `SUPPORT_EMAIL` (default `support@wiamapp.com`) = users / public policy / Play. `COMPANY_EMAIL` (default `labs@wiamapp.com`) = team accounts, QA dashboards, internal ops. Override via env on Render if needed.
- **Deploy:** Pushing to GitHub (`master` on the connected repo) backs up the codebase and **Render deploys from that Git connection automatically**ŌĆödo not add duplicate ŌĆ£trigger deployŌĆØ workflows unless auto-deploy is disabled in the Render dashboard.
